Module com.bcs2024.knapsack
Package com.bcs2024.knapsack.algorithm.dancinglinks

Class DLSearch

java.lang.Object
com.bcs2024.knapsack.algorithm.dancinglinks.DLSearch
public class DLSearch extends Object
DLSearch orchestrates the search process using the Dancing Links algorithm for the knapsack problem. It manages the creation of all possible parcel positions within the cargo space and initiates the algorithm to find the optimal arrangement.

  • Method Details

    • createPositions

      public void createPositions()
      Iterates through all parcels and their rotations, attempting to place them in all possible positions within the cargo space. It then creates a sparse matrix representation of these positions and uses the DancingLinks instance to solve the exact cover problem.

    • canPlace

      public boolean canPlace(int startX, int startY, int startZ, int[][][] shape)
      Checks if a piece can be placed at a specified location within the cargo space. It considers the dimensions of the piece and the boundaries of the cargo space.
      Parameters:
      startX - The starting X-coordinate in the cargo space.
      startY - The starting Y-coordinate in the cargo space.
      startZ - The starting Z-coordinate in the cargo space.
      shape - The 3D array representing the shape of the piece.
      Returns:
      true if the piece can be placed; false otherwise.
